results.title: 9.5mm Pathé-Baby camera and projector
results.brief_description: The Pathé-Baby camera and projector was an inexpensive and easy-to-use amateur film system introduced in 1922. It used 9.5mm film with central perforations.

constellations_primary.name: 9.5mm Pathe-Baby and parents behaving badly
constellations_primary.description: A look at the link between the Pathé-Baby system and animation, as well as the relationship between cinematic parents and their children.

results.description:
The Pathé-Baby camera and projector was an inexpensive and easy-to-use amateur film system introduced in 1922. It used 9.5mm film with central perforations. This unique film width made it easy to duplicate commercial films for home use, and the hand-cranked projector took up to 60 feet of film.

The portability and simplicity of the Pathé-Baby made the system widely popular internationally. This one was used by pioneering Australian aviator John Robertson Duigan MC to document early aviation and his home life. Having built the first Australian-made aircraft, Duigan definitely had something worth capturing.

results.title: Rome
results.brief_description:
Episode of Series “A Practical guide to Europe”.
Presented by John Guerrasio, this is an ideal video for intending travelers to Rome (or Italy generally). Tips and practical advice is given as to accommodation, transportation, places to eat, historical sites to visit, seasonal times to avoid, and suggestions of where to go and what to do whilst in Rome. Also provides a map pointing out the location of major sight-seeing destinations, what to do and what not to do to in respect of Italian culture and customs, and generally assist you in making your visit to Rome an enjoyable experience.

results.title: Paris
results.brief_description:
Episode of Series “A Practical guide to Europe”.
A practical guide for anyone intending to travel to Paris. Highlights the major cultural attractions, historical districts and shopping precincts. Provides advice on public transport options and locating suitable accommodation. Offers tips on visiting galleries and museums during free or quiet periods. Suggests where to eat and what you should expect to pay. Includes the Eiffel Tower, the Louvre, Disneyland, Fountainbleau and Versailles. Presented by John Guerrasio.
